Four hours have gone by with no information coming out of Monday’s African National Congress’ (ANC) National Executive Committee meeting that is widely expected to finalise the fate of beleaguered SA President Jacob Zuma, who has refused his party’s requests to step down.

Cyril Ramaphosa, the deputy president, took over the leadership of the ANC in December in a hotly contested election.
The closed meeting is taking place at Saint Georges Hotel in Irene.
Opposition parties want National Assembly to be dissolved





